{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS-1 review [T5c Security overlay]: PASS (not-applicable).\n\nThis plan reinstates internal latency/cost telemetry (coverage['metrics'] = det_ms/llm_ms/total_ms/llm_calls/claim_path) on a LOCAL plan-review gate of a git-backed tool. Per the overlay's not-applicable clause, no new security surface is added in this application's actual domain: no new endpoint, no network exposure, no authn/authz boundary, no PII, and no credential/secret/grant. The captured data is non-sensitive numeric step timings + counts plus a fixed descriptive marker string. The `claim_path` marker references that the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify, but this plan neither stores, transmits, nor logs any key/secret material — it only records the constant marker. No findings."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782546244307862001,"uuid":"32d4e1dc-b60d-4c22-8f9a-f0ad430f8550"}